        "content": "<p>This response is a bit late, so you might have figured this out by now, but note that inlining works as long as you call <code>LCNF.compile</code> <em>separately</em> on <code>#[`bar]</code> first!</p>\n<p>I guess <code>LCNF.compile #[name1, name2]</code> doesn’t take into account the result of compiling <code>name1</code> when compiling <code>name2</code>. I’m not sure if this is intentional or not. (Parallelism, maybe?)</p>",
